"1222":"1222","1188":"1188","Saint-Jean d'Acre, Palestine, Israel":"Acre, Northern, Israel","Noyon, Oise, Picardie, France":"Noyon, Oise, Picardie, France","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Noyers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): variant of   Bowyer  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bowyer","meanings":["English: occupational name for a maker or seller of bows, or an archer, from Middle English <i>bowyere</i>, an agent derivative of Old English <i>boga</i> ‘bow’. Compare   Bowman  ."]}]},{"name":"Milon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin a local name from the numerous places so called, a large number of which get their name from Old English <i>mylentūn</i> ‘settlement with a mill’. Others were originally named as ‘the middle settlement (of three)’, from Old English <i>middel</i> ‘middle’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’. The surname is most famous as that of the poet  John Milton  (  1608–74 ), and the given name is sometimes bestowed in his honour. Its most illustrious bearer in recent times has been the economist  Milton Friedman  (  1912–2006 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"VII","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Victor ."],"variants":[{"name":"Victor","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name meaning ‘conqueror’. This was popular among early Christians as a reference to Christ's victory over death and sin, and was borne by several saints. An influence on the choice of the name in more recent times was the American actor  Victor Mature  (  1915–99 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Milon VII de Noyers was born in 1185, in Noyon, Oise, Picardie, France as the son of Seigneur Clerembaud de Noyers and Ada de Pleurs. He had at least 2 sons and 3 daughters with Agnès de Brienne. He died on 21 September 1250, in his hometown, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1185–21 September 1250":"1185–21. september 1250","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1188–1222":"1188–1222","1189–Female":"1189–Surnud","1189–1234":"1189–1234","1213–1271":"8.jaanuar1213kuni7.jaanuar1214–1271","1220–1278":"1220–1278","–1246":"–1246","–1267":"–1267","1150–1196":"1150–1196","–1225":"–1225","environ 1220":"umbes 1220","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1196":"1196","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1271":"1271","21 September 1250":"21. september 1250","after 1225":"pärast 1225","1225":"1225","1213":"8. jaanuar 1213 kuni 7. jaanuar 1214","1246":"1246","1234":"1234","1267":"1267","1278":"1278","1189":"1189","1222":"1222","1188":"1188","Saint-Jean d'Acre, Palestine, Israel":"Acre, Northern, Iisrael","Noyon, Oise, Picardie, France":"Noyon, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1185–21 September 1250":"1185–21. syyskuuta 1250","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1188–1222":"1188–1222","1189–Female":"1189–Kuollut","1189–1234":"1189–1234","1213–1271":"vuodesta8.tammikuuta1213vuoteen7.tammikuuta1214–1271","1220–1278":"1220–1278","–1246":"–1246","–1267":"–1267","1150–1196":"1150–1196","–1225":"–1225","environ 1220":"noin 1220","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1196